[b]TVO - The Agenda with Steve Paikin, November 28 2012: Are &quot;Binders Full of Women&quot; Needed?[/b]

[u]Are &quot;Binders Full of Women&quot; Needed?[/u]

The Agenda hears criticism that there aren't enough female guests on our programs. We've blogged about it. Producers have spoken about it online. Now, The Agenda asks: If women are half of Ontario's population, why are they underrepresented in the media?

[u]Guests:[/u]

[b]Jordan Peterson[/b] - Professor of Psychology, University of Toronto

[b]Armine Yalnizyan[/b] - Senior Economist, Canadian Centre for Policy Alternatives

[b]Kathy English[/b] - Public Editor, Toronto Star

[b]Shari Graydon[/b] - Founder, Informed Opinions 

